description: Decimal expansion of imaginary part of solution to z = log z.
comments: Repeatedly take logs, starting from any number not equal to 0, 1, e, e^e, e^(e^e), etc. and you will converge to 0.31813150... + 1.33723570...*I.
references: Wolfram Research, Mathematica, Version 4.1.0.0, Help Browser, under the function FixedPoint.
links: Stanislav Sykora, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..2000
